{
  "number": 307,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/307",
  "title": "Allow debouncing image loading on hit templates",
  "body": "Following #302, it seems that in some situations we could allow users to debounce the image loading.\n\nOne solution:\n\n`hits({container, lazyloadImages})`\n\nOn the implementation side:\n- Users will have to use `ais-src=real-src.jpg` on images + `src={helpers.lazySrc}`\n- We listen to onload on main hits container\n- If onload element === img && img.ais-src => load the image in 100ms\n- If newsearch before 100ms, discard all previous images\n- We can use classes and shit to allow displaying images with fadein fadeout\n\nI think we should not try to lazyload for now (only load what's visible), this is a harder topic to include as an API\n",
  "created_at": "2015-10-21T10:08:24Z",
